<br>
<br>
1)  Add it to the list of 100 items we summon everytime we log on, for ourselves, and use it to get out of a messy messy situation, at the cost of 105pp.<br>
<br>
That's the only reason I can think to use this, ever.  But if it's in PoP, all you have to do is sit in the graveyard for 5 minutes, a cleric will zone in and rez you when you offer them a T-rod.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
Breaking down my reasoning:<br>
<br>
1)  Melee's can buy gate potions cheaper.<br>
2)  You can make your own a hell of alot cheaper with pottery.<br>
3)  It's NO RENT.  When you die and repop in PoM, you can't just summon up a new one and gate to PoK, unless your the only person in the game that repops with reagents on you.<br>
4)  Raids:  How many large scale raids don't have an evaccer?  Or a wizard to TLC the melee's out after the raid is complete?  If you click &quot;yes&quot; here, your guild has some technical issues.<br>
5)  Stock up on Reagent Conservation IV items, and take your chances everytime?  I don't think so.<br>
<br>
<br>
If this is the solution Verant came up with to better the mages odds of survival if the pet dies, or we happen to not have a pet up......we're gunna need a &quot;get-rich-quick&quot; scheme.<br>
<br>
Please respond if I've posted misinformation here.  Peace out. <p>&lt;IMG SRC=http://members.aol.com/valhegen/images/loathexx1.jpg&gt;<br>
